cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use rlox in your research, please cite it using these metadata."
title: "rlox: Rust-Accelerated Reinforcement Learning"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Kowalinski"
    given-names: "Wojciech"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-03-15
license: MIT OR Apache-2.0
url: "https://github.com/riserally/rlox"
repository-code: "https://github.com/riserally/rlox"
abstract: >-
  rlox is a reinforcement learning library that applies the Polars
  architecture pattern (Rust data plane + Python control plane via PyO3)
  to RL. Environments step in Rust with Rayon work-stealing parallelism;
  GAE, replay buffers, and LLM post-training operations run as native
  Rust code; Python stays in charge of training logic and neural networks
  via PyTorch. Delivers 3-140x speedups over SB3 and TorchRL.
keywords:
  - reinforcement-learning
  - rust
  - python
  - pyo3
  - ppo
  - sac
  - dqn
  - grpo
  - dpo
